The paper discusses the evaluation of knowledge organization systems (KOSs) using quantitative informetric measures and indicators. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including information retrieval (cs.IR), digital libraries (cs.DL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and databases (cs.DB). However, since the paper focuses on the analysis and evaluation of KOSs, which are primarily used in information retrieval and digital libraries, cs.IR and cs.DL are the most likely sub-categories. The other sub-categories are also relevant, but to a lesser extent.
